div.p:
I wish you success in your campaign against the Chancellor of the Exchequer, William Pitt (1759–1806;
                           DNB) returned to office as Chancellor, the first minister in the government, in April 1804. & the Emperor of the French Napoleon Bonaparte (1769–1821; First Consul 1799–1804; Emperor of the French 1804–1814). – but I wish also that some cessation of hostilities may
                   enable you to escape from Westminster, & Welsh campaigning, that as you introduced me to Snowdon I may in my turn introduce you to Skiddaw.
